Sense Bus implementation:

  Summary: Enhanced ω Computation via Hexagonal Architecture

  New Files Created

  1. src/yrsn/ports/reliability.py - Port interface defining:
    - IReliabilityMonitor protocol (Sense Bus interface)
    - ReliabilitySignals dataclass (bundles signals 4-7)
    - ReliabilitySignalComputer utility class (signal computation)
  2. src/yrsn/adapters/outbound/reliability.py - Adapter implementations:
    - ReliabilityMonitorAdapter - aggregates existing monitors
    - StandaloneReliabilityMonitor - self-contained history tracking
  3. tests/test_reliability_monitor.py - 24 tests covering all components

  Modified Files

  1. src/yrsn/core/memory/base_learner.py:
    - Added reliability_monitor parameter to __init__
    - Enhanced compute_omega() to use 7 signals (was 3)
    - Added compute_omega_detailed() for observability
  2. src/yrsn/ports/__init__.py - exports new port classes
  3. src/yrsn/adapters/outbound/__init__.py - exports new adapters

  Signal Architecture (Sense Bus)

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │                  compute_omega() - 7 Signals                 │
  ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ CORE SIGNALS (local)         │ SENSE BUS SIGNALS (port)     │
  │ ────────────────────         │ ──────────────────────       │
  │ 1. SDM read confidence       │ 4. Consistency (α variance)  │
  │ 2. Hopfield retrieval conf   │ 5. Trend (α direction)       │
  │ 3. Replay buffer similarity  │ 6. Decision stability        │
  │                              │ 7. Hidden coherence          │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                          ▲
                                          │
                      ┌───────────────────┴───────────────────┐
                      │        IReliabilityMonitor            │
                      │   (StochasticStability + Collapse)    │
                      └───────────────────────────────────────┘

  Usage Example

  from yrsn.adapters.outbound import ReliabilityMonitorAdapter
  from yrsn.core.control import StochasticStabilityMonitor, EarlyCollapseMonitor

  # Connect existing monitors to Sense Bus
  stability = StochasticStabilityMonitor()
  collapse = EarlyCollapseMonitor()
  reliability = ReliabilityMonitorAdapter(stability, collapse)

  # Use with BaseLearner
  config = BaseLearnerConfig(compute_omega=True)
  learner = MyLearner(config, reliability_monitor=reliability)

  # Now compute_omega() uses all 7 signals
  omega = learner.compute_omega(**context)

  This keeps functionality trackable within the hex architecture as requested, with no new storage added - all data comes from existing monitors.
